&lt;h2&gt;Snapshot&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a critical and high impact strategic role that will drive AI strategy, infrastructure investments and AI product portfolio optimization across Google. The role sits within Google DeepMind’s Technology Strategy (TechStrat) function and is a leadership role within Techstrat’s Compute team. Since compute has become the key ingredient for AI model leadership, AI serving success and next generation AI research, this leader will drive high impact decisions that will define the success of Google, with implications on the future of AI for the world.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;About us&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Artificial Intelligence could be one of humanity’s most useful inventions. At Google DeepMind, we’re a team of scientists, engineers, machine learning experts and more, working together to advance the state of the art in artificial intelligence. We use our technologies for widespread public benefit and scientific discovery, and collaborate with others on critical challenges, ensuring safety and ethics are the highest priority.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;The role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As one of the key senior leaders of the compute Tech Strategy team, this role will own the success of our AI strategy by driving the maximal product impact for Google and AI impact for humanity. This leader will have the responsibility of framing key strategic decisions for our SVP+ leadership group based on deep analysis of the situation including value at stake from AI investments, investment optimization options, Industry understanding, financial modeling, product strategy analysis and understanding. They will be constantly looking for opportunities to push the envelope of impact from our investments in AI and inspire the team to do the same. This leader will also drive the synthesis of the situation into SVP+ consumable frameworks and crisp grounded and data backed options. They will then ensure the strategy is executed flawlessly partnering with a multitude of cross functional teams and stakeholders.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Personally drive and amplify impact through leading a team to&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate and drive clarity on some of Google’s hardest long range strategic questions in AI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create new and partner with existing virtual teams across Google to create comprehensive product and policy plans that stand the test of time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Model scenarios and various tradeoffs to create opinionated strategies for maximizing AI value and optimizing AI investments across Google&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create SVP+ forum content (presentations, communications, mandates)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help develop a per-mandate monitoring view to keep programs accountable&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with operational teams and forums in AI&amp;nbsp; to ensure that company-wide SVP+mandates are set up for success -- well organized, staffed and delivering on desired goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay connected across Google to maintain a living catalog of ongoing experiments &amp;amp; proposed innovations that may become worthy of discussion at NRC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify gaps in our processes and information and propose/implement solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
